Welcome to the experiment on decision making with moving dot stimuli!

Thank you for accepting the HIT.

This is a psychological study by the Knowledge, Information, and Learning Laboratory at the University of Melbourne.

There will be four parts to this experiment.

1. Short survey asking for demographic information (approx. 2 minutes)

2. Measurement Task (approx. 5 minutes)

3. Practice (approx. 10 minutes)

4. Main Experiment (approx. 20 minutes)

At the end of the experiment, we will provide you with a survey completion code that you need to get paid for the HIT.

For this experiment, you will be paid $5 plus a bonus depending on your performance in the main experiment.

Please do not press the back button at any point or your progress will be lost!

Please press SPACE to begin.

Practice

The purpose of the practice block is to familiarize you with the moving dot stimuli used in the main experiment.

There is 1 block of 60 practice trials.

On each trial, you will be asked to indicate if the dots in the circle (the \"patch\") are moving left (by pressing 'f') or right (by pressing 'j').

Please respond as quickly and accurately as possible.

You will be told whether you are correct or incorrect.

This task will increase in difficulty across the block of 60 trials.

Press N to begin the practice trials.
